      "front": "What is clustering in Machine Learning?",
      "back": "Clustering is a type of unsupervised machine learning algorithm that groups similar data points into clusters based on their attributes or features."
    },
    {
      "front": "What are the main types of proximity measures used in clustering?",
      "back": "The main types of proximity measures used in clustering are: Euclidean distance, Manhattan distance, Minkowski distance, and Cosine similarity."
